  "prompt": "What are the most common fee structures charged for PPC Management being used by individuals and companies today?",
  "response": "Here are the most common PPC management fee structures:\n\n1. Percentage of Ad Spend\n- Most common approach\n- Typically 10-20% of total monthly ad spend\n- Often with a minimum monthly fee ($500-$1500)\n- Scales with client's advertising budget\n- Incentivizes optimization and growth\n\n2. Flat Monthly Retainer\n- Fixed monthly fee regardless of ad spend\n- Usually ranges $1,000-$5,000\n- Predictable cost for clients\n- Common for small to mid-size businesses\n\n3. Hourly Rate\n- Charged by hours worked\n- Typically $100-$250 per hour\n- Best for smaller, project-based work\n- Less common for ongoing management\n\n4. Performance-Based Pricing\n- Fee tied to specific campaign outcomes\n- Commission on conversions or sales\n- Can include base management fee plus performance bonus\n- Aligns agency incentives with client goals\n\n5. Tiered Pricing Model\n- Different pricing levels based on complexity\n- Varies by budget, industry, campaign sophistication\n- Allows customized service packages\n\n6. Hybrid Models\n- Combination of percentage + flat fee\n- Blended approach for flexibility\n- Tailored to specific client needs\n\nFactors influencing pricing: campaign complexity, industry, competition, agency expertise.",
